The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Tuesday, August 31, 2004 				 Artists communiqu 
																								Founded eight years ago to promote art and culture, Shilpa Sarit is an organisation that believes in getting members of the art community to interact with one another in a way as to generate fresh ideas and positive inspiration for their art. Its annual shows, providing a platform for highly absorbing discussions on art, are occasions looked forward to by senior and junior artists, art critics, art historians and art buyers alike. Shilpa Sarits on-going eighth annual show has on display 66 fine pieces of art works created by several well-known artists including Paritosh Sen, KG Subramanian, Amitava Banerji and Shyamal Dutta Ray, along with a number of contemporary artists from Bengal and beyond. Featuring a wide variety of paintings in different styles and media, the exhibition is a veritable feast of colours and forms. Ashok Gangulys Sati, which appears above, bears testimony to the sheer visual delight as well as spiritual stimulation in store for visitors to this exhibition.																								Event: Shilpa Sarits eighth annual exhibition of painting and sculpture 																								When: Till September 12 (except Mondays); 11 am - 8 pm																								Where: Akar Prakar, P-238 Hindustan Park
